Mary Cowan taught at George Watson's College in Edinburgh and passed away in November last year . 
  She stated in her will that £700,000 of her £2million fortune should be left to charity groups . 
  Ms Cowan asked for a bursary scheme to be set up in her name at the school . 
  She taught famous faces such as Sir Chris Hoy and Gavin Hastings . 
  The 92-year-old also asked for £325,000 to help poorer pupils attend school . 
 